    "slug": "intense-heat-weather",
    "description": "<p><strong>Intense Heat</strong> is the supercharged sunshine that causes droughts - withering plants and dehydrating all that are present. Fire-Types benefit the most, although the effects on all other Types are more pronounced.</p><p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Effects:</span></strong></p><ul><li>For the purposes of Abilities, Attacks, Perks, and Traits, this Weather is considered to also be “Sunny”.</li><li>Fire-Type Attacks deal 60% more damage, and all Water-Type Attacks fail to activate.</li><li>Grass-Type creatures gain 60% to their Movement Allowances, and their SPD is increased 30%, but lose a Tick of HP at the end of their Activations.</li><li>Fire-Type Attacks are one step more effective on all Types, and are super effective against Water-Types.</li><li>Creatures cannot be Frozen, and Frozen creatures are cured of Frozen.</li><li>Non-Fire-, Grass-, Rock-, and Ground Types have -1 default DEF.</li><li>Fire-Type Moves and Physical-Category Steel-Type attacks have a 25% chance to inflict Burn 5. Attacks that would already cause Burn instead increase their chance to Burn by 25%.</li></ul>"
  },
